The Chronicle Nqobile Bhebhe, Senior Reporter HUNDREDS of small-scale formal traders lost furniture and equipment worth millions of dollars early Wednesday morning when fire gutted and reduced the Mpopoma Outspan factory to rubble. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-673961" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/1-1-680x366.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="366" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/1-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/1-1-360x194.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The fire broke out around 5:45 am in a small section of the vast factory and quickly spread to engulf a huge section of the factory. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-673963" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/2-2-680x368.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="368" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/2-2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/2-2-360x195.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The factory, popularly known as Spamprekini is situated along Nketa Drive adjacent to Mpopoma Park. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-673965" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/3-1-680x369.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="369" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/3-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/3-1-360x195.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />
When the Chronicle news crew arrived at the scene around 6 am, scores of workers including women with babies strapped on their backs were battling to salvage their wares in the blazing fire. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-673966" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/4-680x368.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="368" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/4.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/4-360x195.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />
Firefighters were also making frantic efforts to extinguish the fire. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-673967" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/6-680x365.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="365" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/6.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/6-360x193.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The factory produces high-end sofas, wardrobes, kitchen units, tables, and wooden doors as per customer specifications. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-673970" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/9-680x367.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="367" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/9.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/9-360x194.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Although the exact cause of the fire is not yet ascertained, several workers said there was a gas leak. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-673971" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/7-680x366.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="366" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/7.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/7-360x194.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> “I am not 100 percent sure what caused the fire but we highly suspect it was a gas leak.  The factory, a source of our livelihood for decades, no longer exist” said Amos Dlamini. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-673973" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/11-680x366.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="366" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/11.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/11-360x194.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Mpopoma Outspan Association Vice chairman Mr Voice Moyo said members are devastated. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-673975" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/rub-680x368.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="368" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/rub.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/rub-360x195.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> “We are in deep shock, devastated by what happened here. We have lost everything.  Millions of finished products, materials and equipment have been lost. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-673976" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/rub2-680x367.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="367" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/rub2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/rub2-360x194.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> “We appeal to the Government to speedily assist us to get back on our feet,” said Moyo who has been working at the factory since 1996. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-673978" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/3-2-680x369.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="369" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/3-2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/3-2-360x195.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> By mid-morning, fire fighters had managed to contain the fire. more to follow…